`Ideal.map` of `P.I` under `ŌÜ ‚ąė algebraMapD P T s_0`. Combined with
the source-side identity `locIdeal_pow_eq` (T090), this gives the
explicit shape of the image of `(locIdeal P T s_0) ^ n` under the
restricted hom.

**Mathematical content**: `locIdeal P T s_0 = Ideal.map (algebraMapD P
T s_0) P.I` (definition). Applying `Ideal.map ŌÜ` and composing with
`Ideal.map_map` gives `Ideal.map ŌÜ (locIdeal P T s_0) = Ideal.map
