the source open-ideal exponent witness `(Nopen, hN)` from the source
`hopen` (i.e., `(P, T, s_0, Nopen, hN)`), target depth `i`, there
exists a source depth `j` such that for all `y ‚ąą locNhd P T s_0 (j +
Nopen)`,

```
((algebraMap A (Localization.Away s_0) s)^N * divByS 1 s_0) * y ‚ąą
  locNhd P T s_0 i.
```

**Mathematical content**: factor the multiplication as `(algebraMap
s^N) * (divByS 1 s_0 * y)`. Apply T095's one-step `divByS 1 s_0`
shift to push `divByS 1 s_0 * y` from depth `j' + Nopen` to depth
`j'`. Apply T096's `algebraMap` shift at `a := s^N` to push
`algebraMap s^N * (depth-`j'` element)` to depth `i`. Combined: a
single `+ Nopen` shift suffices.

**Side discipline**: this is the **source-side** counterpart to T097's
`locNhd_radInverseFactor_mul_step_of_hopen`. The factor `divByS 1
s_0` here lives in source Loc and needs the **source's** open-ideal
exponent `(P, T, s_0, Nopen, hN)`. **Do not confuse** with T097's
target-side `(P, T, s, Nopen, hN)` instantiation.

**Consumer instantiation hint** (T089): Primary applies this with
`(P, T, s_0) := (D‚āÄ.P, D‚āÄ.T, D‚āÄ.s)`. From `obtain ‚ü®Nopen, hN‚ü© :=
D‚āÄ.hopen` (the **source's** open-ideal exponent), instantiate at
`s := D.s` and `N := N_rad` (from `rad_relation_of_rational_subset
D‚āÄ D h`, which gives `e_rad * D‚āÄ.s = D.s ^ N_rad`). The resulting
shift controls the depth of the multiplied-by-source-rewrite-factor
element in the **source** `locNhd D‚āÄ` filtration. -/
theorem locNhd_radSourceFactor_mul_step_of_hopen
    (P : PairOfDefinition A) (T : Finset A) (s_0 : A)
    (Nopen : ‚Ąē) (hN : ‚ąÄ b : P.A‚āÄ, b ‚ąą P.I ^ Nopen ‚Üí
      divByS (‚ÜĎb : A) s_0 ‚ąą locSubring P T s_0)
    (i : ‚Ąē) (s : A) (N : ‚Ąē) :
    ‚ąÉ j : ‚Ąē, ‚ąÄ y ‚ąą locNhd P T s_0 (j + Nopen),
      ((algebraMap A (Localization.Away s_0) s) ^ N *
        divByS 1 s_0) * y ‚ąą locNhd P T s_0 i := by
  -- algebraMap (s^N) = (algebraMap s)^N, so multiplication by the
  -- source factor reduces to T096 algebraMap shift at `a := s^N`
  -- composed with T095 one-step divByS shift.
  obtain ‚ü®j, hj‚ü© :=
    locNhd_algMap_mul_step_of_hopen P T s_0 ‚ü®Nopen, hN‚ü© i (s ^ N)
  refine ‚ü®j, fun y hy => ?_‚ü©
  have h_step : divByS 1 s_0 * y ‚ąą locNhd P T s_0 j :=
    locNhd_invS_step_of_hopen P T s_0 Nopen hN j y hy
  have h_algMap :
      algebraMap A (Localization.Away s_0) (s ^ N) *
        (divByS 1 s_0 * y) ‚ąą locNhd P T s_0 i :=
    hj _ h_step
  rwa [map_pow, ‚Üź mul_assoc] at h_algMap

/-! ## Generic small-mod-kernel representative bridge (T099)

Reusable algebraic bridge for T089's corrected residual: extracting a
"small" representative `b` modulo `ker(locLift)` from a sum decomposition
`a ‚ąą sourceSmall + ker(locLift)`. The general statement is:

```
For any AddMonoidHom `f : G ‚Üí+ H` between AddCommGroups and any
AddSubgroup `U ‚Č§ G`, if `a ‚ąą U ‚äĒ f.ker` then ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą U, f b = f a.
```

The proof is a one-liner: `a ‚ąą U ‚äĒ f.ker` unfolds (via
`AddSubgroup.mem_sup'`) to `a = u + k` with `u ‚ąą U`, `k ‚ąą f.ker`, then
`b := u` works since `f a = f u + f k = f u + 0 = f u`.

**Deliverables**:

* `AddSubgroup.exists_mem_of_mem_sup_ker` ‚ÄĒ generic AddMonoidHom form
  on AddCommGroups.

* `RingHom.exists_mem_of_mem_sup_ker` ‚ÄĒ RingHom wrapper using
  `f.toAddMonoidHom.ker`. Convenient when working with ring-hom
  kernels in the AddSubgroup setting.

* `locNhd_exists_small_repr_of_mem_sup_ker` ‚ÄĒ `locNhd`-specialised
  wrapper: from `a ‚ąą locNhd P T s n ‚äĒ f.toAddMonoidHom.ker`, obtain
  `b ‚ąą locNhd P T s n` with `f b = f a`. Direct specialisation of
  the RingHom version at `U := locNhd P T s n` (which is an
  `AddSubgroup (Localization.Away s)`).

**Consumer usage** (T089): from `a ‚ąą sourceSmall + ker(locLift)`
(typically `sourceSmall := locNhd D‚āÄ.P D‚āÄ.T D‚āÄ.s n` and `ker(locLift)
:= (locLift D‚āÄ D h).toAddMonoidHom.ker`), obtain `b ‚ąą sourceSmall`
with `locLift b = locLift a` via
`locNhd_exists_small_repr_of_mem_sup_ker D‚āÄ.P D‚āÄ.T D‚āÄ.s n (locLift D‚āÄ
D h) ha`.

**Mathlib precedent**: the underlying combinator
`AddSubgroup.mem_sup'` (`x ‚ąą s ‚äĒ t ‚ÜĒ ‚ąÉ y z, ‚ÜĎy + ‚ÜĎz = x`) is the
standard mathlib characterisation; the small-representative theorem
just composes it with the kernel-membership unfolding. Mathlib doesn't
seem to have this exact composed form, so we land it here as a
public reusable lemma. -/

omit [IsTopologicalRing A] in
/-- **Generic small representative mod kernel** (T099 reusable
mathlib-style primitive).

For any `AddMonoidHom f : G ‚Üí+ H` between AddCommGroups and any
AddSubgroup `U ‚Č§ G`, if `a ‚ąą U ‚äĒ f.ker`, then there exists `b ‚ąą U`
with `f b = f a`.

**Mathematical content**: `a ‚ąą U ‚äĒ f.ker` decomposes as `a = u + k`
with `u ‚ąą U` and `k ‚ąą f.ker` (via `AddSubgroup.mem_sup'`). Setting
`b := u` gives `f b = f u = f u + f k = f (u + k) = f a` (using `f k =
0` from the kernel membership).

**Use**: lets a consumer extract a "small" representative (in `U`)
sharing the `f`-image with `a`, mod the kernel of `f`. This is the
reusable algebraic engine behind T089's
"locLift‚ĀĽ¬Ļ(target locNhd) ‚äÜ source locNhd + ker(locLift) ‚áí small
representative" assembly. -/
theorem AddSubgroup.exists_mem_of_mem_sup_ker
    {G H : Type*} [AddCommGroup G] [AddCommGroup H]
    (f : G ‚Üí+ H) (U : AddSubgroup G) {a : G}
    (ha : a ‚ąą U ‚äĒ f.ker) :
    ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą U, f b = f a := by
  obtain ‚ü®u, k, rfl‚ü© := AddSubgroup.mem_sup'.mp ha
  refine ‚ü®u, u.property, ?_‚ü©
  rw [map_add, AddMonoidHom.mem_ker.mp k.property, add_zero]

omit [IsTopologicalRing A] in
/-- **RingHom small representative mod kernel** (T099 ring-hom wrapper).

For any RingHom `f : R ‚Üí+* S` between rings (with `R` a Ring giving an
AddCommGroup structure) and any AddSubgroup `U ‚Č§ R`, if `a ‚ąą U ‚äĒ
f.toAddMonoidHom.ker`, then there exists `b ‚ąą U` with `f b = f a`.

Direct wrapper of `AddSubgroup.exists_mem_of_mem_sup_ker` for the ring-
hom case. The kernel here is `f.toAddMonoidHom.ker : AddSubgroup R`,
not `RingHom.ker f : Ideal R`; for the Ideal-level form, callers can
use `Submodule.toAddSubgroup` to pass through.

**Use**: ring-hom version of the small-mod-kernel extraction; the
`toAddMonoidHom.ker` gives us the AddSubgroup form needed for the
underlying lemma. -/
theorem RingHom.exists_mem_of_mem_sup_ker
    {R S : Type*} [Ring R] [Ring S] (f : R ‚Üí+* S) (U : AddSubgroup R)
    {a : R} (ha : a ‚ąą U ‚äĒ f.toAddMonoidHom.ker) :
    ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą U, f b = f a :=
  AddSubgroup.exists_mem_of_mem_sup_ker f.toAddMonoidHom U ha

omit [IsTopologicalRing A] in
/-- **`locNhd` small representative mod kernel** (T099 ticket-named
locNhd-specialised wrapper).

For any RingHom `f : Localization.Away s ‚Üí+* S` and any source `locNhd`
depth `n`, if `a ‚ąą locNhd P T s n ‚äĒ f.toAddMonoidHom.ker`, then there
exists `b ‚ąą locNhd P T s n` with `f b = f a`.

Direct specialisation of `RingHom.exists_mem_of_mem_sup_ker` at `U :=
locNhd P T s n` (which is an `AddSubgroup (Localization.Away s)`).

**Consumer usage** (T089, one-line):
```
obtain ‚ü®b, hb, hfb‚ü© :=
  locNhd_exists_small_repr_of_mem_sup_ker D‚āÄ.P D‚āÄ.T D‚āÄ.s n
    (locLift D‚āÄ D h) ha
```
where `ha : a ‚ąą locNhd D‚āÄ.P D‚āÄ.T D‚āÄ.s n ‚äĒ
(locLift D‚āÄ D h).toAddMonoidHom.ker`. The result `b ‚ąą locNhd D‚āÄ.P
D‚āÄ.T D‚āÄ.s n` is the source-small representative; `hfb : locLift D‚āÄ D
h b = locLift D‚āÄ D h a` confirms the same `locLift`-image. -/
theorem locNhd_exists_small_repr_of_mem_sup_ker
    (P : PairOfDefinition A) (T : Finset A) (s : A) (n : ‚Ąē)
    {S : Type*} [Ring S] (f : Localization.Away s ‚Üí+* S)
    {a : Localization.Away s}
    (ha : a ‚ąą locNhd P T s n ‚äĒ f.toAddMonoidHom.ker) :
    ‚ąÉ b ‚ąą locNhd P T s n, f b = f a :=
  RingHom.exists_mem_of_mem_sup_ker f (locNhd P T s n) ha

